	<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#003399"><strong><em>	
<a href="../audiovisual/default.asp">Audio Visuals</a> | IRIN Special Photo Report on <a href="http://www.angola.npaid.org/" target="_blank" style="color:#0000ff">Norwegian People's Aid (NPA) De-Mining Operations</a> in Angola, 20 July 1999
	</em></strong></font>
    </td>
  </tr>	
  <tr> 
    <td align="center">
      <table border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="5" width="85%">
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/casspirandsoldier.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/casspirandsoldier_small.jpg" alt="casspirandsoldier.jpg (35691 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">1. Angola 
              has been in a state of almost constant civil war since independence 
              from Portugal in 1974</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/litteredammunition.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/litteredammunition_small.jpg" alt="litteredammunition.jpg (62228 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">2. Aid 
              agencies have identified over 2,000 separate mine and unexploded 
              ordnance (UXO) sites spread throughout the country as a result of 
              the conflict</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/stackedammunition.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/stackedammunition_small.jpg" alt="stackedammunition.jpg (47956 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">3. Efforts 
              to voluntarily disarm Angola's rebels collapsed late last year as 
              a UN-brokered peace accord broke down and both UNITA and government 
              forces returned to full-scale fighting</font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/4x4inwater.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/4x4inwater_small.jpg" alt="4x4inwater.jpg (40820 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">4. However, 
              efforts by groups such as Norwegian People's Aid (NPA) to clear 
              previously mined areas have continued successfully</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/villagersdiscussing.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/villagersdiscussing_small.jpg" alt="villagersdiscussing.jpg (45559 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">5. NPA 
              - the largest de-mining organisation in Angola -&nbsp; is working 
              with local communities in Angola's provinces&nbsp; to prioritise 
              sites for mine removal</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/clearanceplanning.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/clearanceplanning_small.jpg" alt="clearanceplanning.jpg (53495 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">6. Clearance 
              supervisors are called in to plan how to open previously closed 
              areas, such as this agricultural site close to Lucala in Kwanza 
              Norte province</font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/samplingteam.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/samplingteam_small.jpg" alt="samplingteam.jpg (38531 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">7. 
              To speed up road clearance, NPA survey teams work in conjunction 
              with mine blast-protected vehicles to collect air samples from suspected 
              road sections for further explosive vapour analysis using sniffer-dogs</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/snifferdog.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/snifferdog_small.jpg" alt="snifferdog.jpg (37158 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">8. Ten 
              dogs have been trained to respond to air samples collected from 
              suspected road surfaces. Teams of de-miners or machines can then 
              be deployed to concentrate clearance efforts along road sections, 
              which have tested positively</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/doghandler.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/doghandler_small.jpg" alt="doghandler.jpg (50280 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">9. Trained 
              sniffer-dogs can also be used to locate buried mines and UXO directly 
              by reacting to explosive vapour rising from the hidden object</font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/deminercuttingawaygrass.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/deminercuttingawaygrass_small.jpg" alt="deminercuttingawaygrass.jpg (41394 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">10. Once 
              mines have been located, however, the slow and laborious task of 
              removing them begins</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/deminerwithdetector2.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/deminerwithdetector2_small.jpg" alt="deminerwithdetector2.jpg (54429 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">11. Clearing 
              mines by hand is painstaking, difficult and sometimes extremely 
              dangerous work unless strict safety procedures are observed</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/deminerwithdetector.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/deminerwithdetector_small.jpg" alt="deminerwithdetector.jpg (50492 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">12. It 
              can take trained NPA de-miners hours to clear just a few metres 
              of ground</font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/deminerremovingatmine.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/deminerremovingatmine_small.jpg" alt="deminerremovingatmine.jpg (62717 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">13. Adding 
              to the danger, some mines will have become unstable because they 
              have been lying in the ground for a long ime, or, in some cases 
              because they are booby-trapped to hamper clearance efforts</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/aardvarkflailing.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/aardvarkflailing_small.jpg" alt="aardvarkflailing.jpg (30862 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">14. NPA 
              has five mechanical mine-clearance machines, which can significantly 
              increase the speed of de-mining in open terrain</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/aardvarkhammers.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/aardvarkhammers_small.jpg" alt="aardvarkhammers.jpg (45369 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">15. The 
              &quot;Aardvark&quot; flails hammers and chains from a unit at the 
              front of the vehicle to detonate and destroy mines</font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/explosion.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/explosion_small.jpg" alt="explosion.jpg (24391 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">16. An 
              18-tonne Hydrema suffers only minimal damage as it sets off an anti-tank 
              mine</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/minevictim.jpg','width=320,height=460');return false;"><img src="angola/minevictim_small.jpg" alt="minevictim.jpg (38388 bytes)" border="1" width="75" height="100"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">17. NPA 
              de-miners are sometimes at hand when the civilians they are trying 
              to protect sadly become victims before mines can be removed</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/removinguxofromhouse.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/removinguxofromhouse_small.jpg" alt="removinguxofromhouse.jpg (31769 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">18. NPA 
              is often also called upon to remove unexploded munitions from populated 
              areas, such as from this house in Malanje City in northern Angola</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/removingd30shell.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/removingd30shell_small.jpg" alt="removingd30shell.jpg (48837 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">19. Many 
              shells fail to detonate as intended, and instead lie visible or 
              buried ready to explode unexpectedly for months or even years unless 
              they are cleared by specialist teams</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/fuses.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/fuses_small.jpg" alt="fuses.jpg (58241 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">20. NPA 
              teams sort and prepare hundreds of mortar fuses for safe demolition</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/npateam.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/npateam_small.jpg" alt="npateam.jpg (36939 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">21. Dangerous 
              items such as shells - which are in a safe condition to move -&nbsp; 
              are collected together... </font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/loadingammunitioninvehicle.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/loadingammunitioninvehicle_small.jpg" alt="loadingammunitioninvehicle.jpg (47081 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">22. ...and 
              carefully removed to a safe area...</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/npateamindemopit.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/npateamindemopit_small.jpg" alt="npateamindemopit.jpg (47542 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a>
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">23. ...where 
              they can be safely destroyed by controlled explosions in specially-dug 
              demolition pits well away from people and buildings</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/mineawareness.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/mineawareness_small.jpg" alt="mineawareness.jpg (34075 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">24. Mines 
              are frequently laid indiscriminately, unmapped and unmarked. NPA 
              trains local instructors in mine awareness skills to warn people 
              to be careful of suspicious devices and how to reduce the danger 
              of mines</font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/ploughedfield.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/ploughedfield_small.jpg" alt="ploughedfield.jpg (41385 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">25. Land 
              is often cultivated immediately behind the advancing line of cleared 
              area</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/animalsreturningtofields.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/animalsreturningtofields_small.jpg" alt="animalsreturningtofields.jpg (40244 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">26. Llivestock 
              can return to this area cleared for grazing in Huila and Cunene 
              thanks to over 100,000 mines and UXO removed by NPA since 1995</font> 
          </td>
          <td align="center" valign="top"><A href=# onClick="OpenNewWindow('angola/dancing.jpg','width=420,height=360');return false;"><img src="angola/dancing_small.jpg" alt="dancing.jpg (47766 bytes)" border="1" width="100" height="75"></a> 
            <p align="left"><font face="Arial" size="1" color="#000000">27. And 
              everyone in a cleared village rejoices that their lives can return 
              to greater normality now that the immediate danger of mines has 
              been reduced</font> 
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
  </tr>
